GUI Bug 3: attach-backing silently failed -- bogus size guard (FIX APPLIED)
  Symptom (this session): a -gui boot got PAST create-2d (format 0x2
  accepted silently, no "host accepted" line) but printed:
      virtio-gpu: scanout0 1024x768 enabled=1
      virtio-gpu: scanout setup failed
  with NO create-2d / attach-backing / set-scanout error line in
  between, and the 9vz window stayed pure black.  "no preceding
  error" is the whole tell: every failing helper prints its own
  err- line EXCEPT two silent `return -1` paths in
  gpuattachbacking() -- the buf==nil OOM path and a size guard
      if(sz > sizeof(vgpu.cmd)) return -1;
  ROOT CAUSE: that size guard was wrong.  attach-backing builds its
  command in its OWN mallocz(sz) buffer (because the scatter list is
  one virtio_gpu_mem_entry per framebuffer PAGE and can be large),
  NOT in the 1KB gpucmd scratch vgpu.cmd.  For 1024x768x4 the
  framebuffer is 768 pages => sz = 32 (hdr+resid+nentries) +
  768*16 (mementry) = 12320 bytes.  12320 > sizeof(vgpu.cmd)==1024,
  so the guard tripped and returned -1 SILENTLY, surfacing only as
  the generic "scanout setup failed".  The guard was a copy/paste
  leftover from gpucmd()'s real bound; attach-backing does not use
  that buffer at all.
  FIX (screen.c gpuattachbacking): delete the sz>sizeof(vgpu.cmd)
  guard; the command lives in its own buffer whose size is whatever
  the page count requires.  Also gave the remaining OOM path
  (mallocz==nil) a print() so it can never again fail mute.  The
  command is still issued as a single virtio descriptor pointing at
  the contiguous mallocz buffer (kernel pool allocations are
  physically contiguous in the KZERO direct map, the same
  assumption every other PADDR-on-malloc site in the kernel makes).
  UNTESTED -- compiles clean (mk in /sys/src/9/vz64; 9vz.bin
  regenerated).  Next -gui boot should now get create-2d + attach-
  backing + set-scanout all OK and PAINT the orange "Plan 9
  Console" banner.  See the capture list below.

